  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\nI'm having an issue running a simple script from package.json. Here's my script:\r\n`\"e2e\": \"SHARDHAT_BIN=./node_modules/.bin/ts-node npx shardhat e2e/runner.ts\"`\r\n\r\nAnd here's my runner.ts file:\r\n```\r\nimport mocha from 'mocha'\r\n\r\nlet mochaRunner = new mocha();\r\nconsole.log('Test');\r\nmochaRunner.addFile(__dirname + '/e2e.ts')\r\nmochaRunner.run(function(failures) {\r\n    process.exitCode = failures ? 1 : 0;  // exit with non-zero status if there were failures\r\n}); \r\n```\r\n\r\nFor some reasons, When running `npm run e2e`, I get the following error message:\r\n```\r\nnicolas.ma@MacBook-Pro web3-contracts-evm-test-project % npm run e2e --show-stack-traces\r\n\r\n> web3-contracts-evm-test-project@1.0.0 e2e\r\n> SHARDHAT_BIN=./node_modules/.bin/ts-node npx hardhat e2e/runner.ts\r\nError HH303: Unrecognized task e2e/runner.ts\r\nFor more info go to https://hardhat.org/HH303 or run Hardhat with --show-stack-traces\r\n```\r\n\r\nAny idea where this issue comes from ? My file is well located under \"e2e/runner.ts\". It is not mispelled.\r\n",
